WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for MediaTek's Dimensity 9500 flagship
mobile SoC. It defines the Arm C1-Ultra "Blackhawk" CPU cluster (custom
implementation of Armv9.2), the 12-core Mali G1-Ultra GPU, the NPU 990
AI accelerator (~100 TOPS), and the Imagiq 1190 ISP.

WHY IT EXISTS
The Dimensity 9500 is the first mobile SoC to break the 4.2 GHz clock
barrier using a custom "C1" implementation of the Cortex-X925. GIOP
must model its unique memory hierarchy (16 MB L3 + 10 MB SLC) and AI
throughput to correctly predict on-device processing times.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Frequency Scaling (C1-Ultra):
  Perf(f) = Perf_base * (f / f_base) ^ α
  where α ≈ 0.85 (sub-linear due to memory wall), f_base = 2.7 GHz,
  f_max = 4.21 GHz (C1-Ultra), Perf_base = 1.0. Single-core Geekbench 6
  ≈ 3,600 at 4.21 GHz.[reference:7]

CPU Cache Hierarchy:
  L2_cache_hit_rate = 1 - (cache_miss_penalty / L3_latency)
  C1-Ultra: 2 MB L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.94
  C1-Premium: 1 MB L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.89
  C1-Pro: 512 KB L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.82
  16 MB L3 + 10 MB SLC → effective L3 miss rate < 2%.[reference:8]

GPU Throughput (Mali G1-Ultra, 12 cores):
  TFLOPS_FP32 = (cores * ALUs_per_core * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  = (12 * 128 * 2 * 1.1e9) / 1e12 ≈ 3.4 TFLOPS
  Ray tracing frame interpolation at 120 fps via hardware RT cores.
  Efficiency improvement: +42% perf/W over Immortalis-G925. [reference:9]

NPU 990 AI Throughput:
  TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_npu) / 1e12
  ≈ (24,576 * 2 * 2.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 98 TOPS (~100 TOPS marketed).
  Supports agentic AI: real-time LMT suggestion, text-to-LUT generation,
  on-device Stable Diffusion (512×512, ~1.2 s).[reference:10]

ISP Imagiq 1190:
  Supports 200 MP single-shot, 4K 60 fps portrait video with continuous
  autofocus tracking. 18-bit internal pipeline for HDR fusion.[reference:11]

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR5x-10667):
  BW = 8 * 10.667e9 * 2 = 170.7 GB/s[reference:12]

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- vivo X400/X400 Pro, OPPO Find X9/X9 Pro, HONOR Magic7 Pro.
- GIOP on-device AI grading, real-time text-to-LUT, HDR fusion.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers targeting MediaTek-powered devices; L3 Colorists using
on-device AI grading tools.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Models the C1-Ultra custom core and the 26 MB combined cache as auditable
formulas, enabling precise performance prediction for GIOP transforms
running on MediaTek flagships.

